
GadTools Slider Tags
====================

Usage: CreateGadgetA/GTTags
       GT_SetGadgetAttrsA_/GTSetAttrs

GTSL_Min: ( ti_Tag = $80080026 )

Specify in ti_Data the minimum
level of the slider.


GadTools Slider Tags
====================

Usage: CreateGadgetA/GTTags
       GT_SetGadgetAttrsA_/GTSetAttrs

GTSL_Max: ( ti_Tag = $80080027 )

Specify in ti_Data the maximum
level of the slider.


GadTools Slider Tags
====================

Usage: CreateGadgetA/GTTags
       GT_SetGadgetAttrsA_/GTSetAttrs

GTSL_Level: ( ti_Tag = $80080027 )

Specify in ti_Data the initial
or current level of the slider.


GadTools Slider Tags
====================

Usage: CreateGadgetA/GTTags

GTSL_MaxLevelLen: ( ti_Tag = $80080029 )

Specify in ti_Data maximum length
of the string to be created from the
given level-formatting string, which
must be provided by GTSL_LevelFormat
when using this tg.


GadTools Slider Tags
====================

Usage: CreateGadgetA/GTTags

GTSL_LevelFormat: ( ti_Tag = $8008002A )

Specify that the current level of the
slider is to be displayed in real-time
alongside the gadget.
In ti_Data, place a pointer to a null
terminated string including printf 
style formatting.


GadTools Slider Tags
====================

Usage: CreateGadgetA/GTTags

GTSL_LevelPlace: ( ti_Tag = $8008002B )

Specify in ti_Data one of the following
constants, for the positioning of the 
level display:

PLACETEXT_LEFT
PLACETEXT_RIGHT
PLACETEXT_ABOVE
PLACETEXT_BELOW


GadTools Slider Tags
====================

Usage: CreateGadgetA/GTTags

GTSL_DispFunc: ( ti_Tag = $8008002C )

Specify a pointer to a Function, to convert
the slider level into a level to display.
See Rom Kernal Manuals for more details.


GadTools String Tags
====================

Usage: CreateGadgetA/GTTags
       GT_SetGadgetAttrsA_/GTSetAttrs

GTST_String: ( ti_Tag = $8008002D )

Specify a pointer to a Null terminated
string to be the default in the string
gadget.


GadTools String Tags
====================

Usage: CreateGadgetA/GTTags

GTST_MaxChars: ( ti_Tag = $8008002E )

Specify in ti_Data an unsigned word
representing the maximum number of
characters that the text entry gadget 
will allow.


GadTools String Tags
====================

Usage: CreateGadgetA/GTTags
       GT_SetGadgetAttrsA_/GTSetAttrs

GTST_EditHook: ( ti_Tag = $80080037 )

Provide a pointer to a custom editing 
Hook for a String gadget.


GadTools BevelBox Tags
======================

Usage: GTBevelBox/DrawBevelB

GTBB_Recessed: ( ti_Tag = $80080033 )

Provide a boolean True in ti_Data to 
draw a recessed box, False gives 
a raised box.


GadTools Integer Tags
=====================

Usage: CreateGadgetA/GTTags
       GT_SetGadgetAttrsA_/GTSetAttrs

GTIN_Number: ( ti_Tag = $8008002F )

Provide an Unsigned Long in ti_Data
representing the initial/current
integer in the number-entry gadget.


GadTools Integer Tags
=====================

Usage: CreateGadgetA/GTTags

GTIN_MaxChars: ( ti_Tag = $80080030 )

Specify in ti_Data an unsigned word
representing the maximum number of
digits that the number entry gadget 
will allow.


GadTools Palette Tags
=====================

Usage: CreateGadgetA/GTTags

GTPA_Depth: ( ti_Tag = $80080010 )

Specify in ti_Data an unsigned word
to dictate the number of bitplanes
the palette represents.


GadTools Palette Tags
=====================

Usage: CreateGadgetA/GTTags
       GT_SetGadgetAttrsA_/GTSetAttrs

GTPA_Color: ( ti_Tag = $80080011 )

Specify the initial/current selected
color of the palette, in ti_Data.


GadTools Palette Tags
=====================

Usage: CreateGadgetA/GTTags

GTPA_ColorOffset: ( ti_Tag = $80080012 )

Specify in ti_Data, the first color to
use in the palette.


GadTools Palette Tags
=====================

Usage: CreateGadgetA/GTTags

GTPA_IndicatorWidth: ( ti_Tag = $80080013 )

Specify in ti_Data, the required width of
the current color indicator. This Tag implies
that an indicator is needed above the color
selection squares.


GadTools Palette Tags
=====================

Usage: CreateGadgetA/GTTags

GTPA_IndicatorHeight: ( ti_Tag = $80080014 )

Specify in ti_Data, the required height of
the current color indicator. This Tag implies
that an indicator is needed above the color
selection squares.

